reviewText:
Talented compilation of known ideas, too nicely done and addictive enough to be ignored.

It's about:Princess (barely and briefly yet), Pixel, Loot;
dungeon crawling;
cursing the random;
patience and reaction;
jumping;
managing available resources (gold, keys, bombs) for the most efficient use;
daring, trying and dying.
Why you should play this:addictive gameplay - it's kind of fast-paced rogue-like/platformer (one successfull session takes about 30-40 minutes) with clear and simple (but not simplistic) mechanic:
basically, you choose a hero and have to go through 8 levels + 4 fights with bosses (incl. final one);
you explore level room-by-room" and looking for an "exit";
on each level there're: hidden places and locked doors (explode and open them using bombs and keys)
